doctype
html(lang="en")
  head
    title Thenmap
    meta(name="description", content="Thenmap is a repository for historical geodata.")
    meta(name="viewport", content="width=device-width")
    link(rel='stylesheet', href='//maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootswatch/3.3.5/readable/bootstrap.min.css')
    link(rel='stylesheet', href='css/main.css')
  body
    article#main.container
        div.jumbotron.col-sm-10.col-sm-offset-1
          span#logo.icon-map

          h1 Thenmap
          p.intro Thenmap is a repository for historical borders. You can use it to create historical maps, like the one below.

        div.row
          div.col-sm-5.col-sm-offset-1
            h2 Thenmap API         
            p.lead Use the Thenmap API to fetch maps with historically accurate borders as GeoJSON or SVG.
            p Pass a year and preferred projection and the API will give you a map in return. Like a <a href="//api.thenmap.net/v1/world/geo/1956">world map of 1954</a> or a map of <a href="//api.thenmap.net/v1/sweden/geo/1979">Swedish municipalities from 1979</a>.
            p The Thenmap API currently holds <strong>world borders post 1945</strong> and <strong>Swedish municipality borders post 1973</strong>. 
            p Learn more by reading the <a href="//api.thenmap.net">full documentation</a>.

          div.col-sm-5
            h2 Thenmap.js
            p.lead Use Thenmap.js to embed a historical SVG map on your site. 
            p We built a super simple <a href="//github.com/rotsee/thenmap-js">javascript library for Thenmap</a> that lets you draw SVG maps with a few lines of code. You can color the map by defining fill colors in a Google spreadsheet.
            p Look how simple it is:
            pre
              code
                |var settings = {
                |  dataKey: "1xyNmpKKksy7ZaELB12UY4M2CP0-4EkwO7DWpfu30wsE",
                |  dataset: "world",
                |  date: "1949"
                |}
                |Thenmap.init("worldmap", settings);

        div.col-sm-10.col-sm-offset-1
          h2 An example: French colonies in 1949
          figure
            div#worldmap

        script(src="//drvkoaf101245.cloudfront.net/thenmap-1.0.0.min.js")
        script.
            var container = document.getElementById("worldmap");
            var containerWidth = container.offsetWidth;

            var settings = {
              dataKey: "1xyNmpKKksy7ZaELB12UY4M2CP0-4EkwO7DWpfu30wsE",
              dataset: "world",
              date: "1949",
              language: "en",
              defaultColor: "#333",
              width:containerWidth,
              height:containerWidth * 0.4,
            }
            Thenmap.init("worldmap", settings);

        div.col-sm-10.col-sm-offset-1
          p Looking for the old version of this page? Find it at <a class="servicelink" href="//old.thenmap.net">old.thenmap.net</a>.

